item.title: The FBI sting that tore apart a small town
item.description:
The FBI sting that tore apart a small town

For generations, the people of the Four Corners region have battled the federal government over collecting and selling Native American artifacts. Then agents persuaded a local dealer to go undercover. Operation Cerberus Action was supposed to expose a lucrative trade in stolen antiquities. Instead, it tore a hole in a Utah town.

item.title: FBI aerial video answers some questions, raises more...
item.description:
FBI aerial video answers some questions, raises more...

The rapid release of the FBI aerial video showing the events that led up to LaVoy Finicum's death is appreciated. In this day and age where police shooting videos are not released for weeks, months, and even years, the fact that this was done in just a few days is good.

item.title: Complete, Unedited Video of Joint FBI and OSP Operation 01/26/2016
item.description:
Complete, Unedited Video of Joint FBI and OSP Operation 01/26/2016

This is the complete video footage of a joint FBI and Oregon State Police traffic stop and OSP officer-involved shooting of Robert "LaVoy" Finicum along Oregon Highway 395 near milepost 50 in Harney County. This footage, which has only been edited to blur out aircraft information, was taken by the FBI on 01/26/2016 and released by the FBI on 01/28/2016.
